Wimbus, FYI .. there is one situation where a nearly fully popped room *can* be camped (though not in the case highlighted in this thread).<br>
AoE groups.  My guild do AoE groups in Guk doing lord/frenzy etc.  With AoE you want to pull large amounts of mobs at once.  This often means pulling an entire section of your zone, killing it, pulling another section, killing it .. waiting for a repop to give you enough mobs to justify an AoE pull, killing it all again. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bendieq>BendiEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 145<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/11/02 8:30:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1976.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   ...</span><hr size=1> Actually there are several mistakes about camps being made here. Camps are a courtesy, but they have some pretty hardcore delimiters. Killstealing is when someone kills a mob after it has aggroed on you first.... and thats all killstealing is. Killstealing is NOT taking a mob from your camp. <br>
<br>
Camps are certain static spawns/rooms. You cannot camp an entire area of a zone - and it doesn't matter if you are in an AoE group. Just because you are capable of killing 3 rooms, or 3 named in an area, that doesn't mean you have camp rights to all 3. You have camp rights to one, and one only. If someone asks for one, you got to give it up. This most certainly includes area effect groups - and if giving up even one of the sub camps makes an AoE group non viable... well, thats life, you don't get to hog a whole area simply because you can. <br>
<br>
If you leave a camp, you lose the camp. If it reaches full spawn, its not your camp anymore. <br>
<br>
That said, I'm *strongly* suspicious of anyone who acts like Wimbus did in the above post - he was being an ass. He was in the right, but he was being an ass. Though at 32, there are better areas for him to be hunting (mind you, same goes for the mid 20's as well). <br>
