AoE groups do camp areas of zones, get used to it, it happens. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thevolcanogod>thevolcanogod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 353<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/11/02 1:34:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1976.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Wimbus!</span><hr size=1> So the next time I see a person medding in the nobles room of HHK and both are up, can I just leapfrog them and take both spawns and claim the camp? What if another group has cleared Sebilis down to the point of the zone out building and is intending to do NG, can my group leapfrog them as soon as they engage the frogs there and take NG? What about in LGuk if a group is doing AM/Hand and they leave the AM room after clearing it to do hand - can I sneak a group in there and claim AM even thought convention has it that those 2 are usually held together and the other group really hasn't &quot;left the camp&quot;?<br>
<br>
Don't mean to complicate the issue here but every situation is unique - that's why we play an online INTERACTIVE game - because we can interact with other players and find a solution. The idea of camps began long ago before you and I and most people were playing this game. They were a set of loose &quot;community rules&quot; that people held to so that there was some order in the community. VI tried to destroy the idea of camping with the PnP but it endured because the players recognized the need to camp and the need for order. In time, even SOE came around to the point of recognizing the need to camp but not officially accepting the idea of one person or group monopolizing the spawns in a certain area. So we are at the present where camps are generally respected - with some people to a lesser or greater degree - and the big flames you see are mainly bred from misunderstanding and unwillingness to cooperate with a lot of ego and temper thrown in as kindling.<br>
<br>
More than respecting camps, respect your fellow players. Most of them are not out to screw you over. If you only know one place to gain XP for your level range, do more research and look around - I have never been at a point where I don't have at least 3-4 options for good solo XP. It probably took them longer arguing about the whole fiasco than it would for one to leave and relocate somewhere else and there is all the hurt feeling in the process.<br>
<br>
Bald, most AoE groups like to find some out-of-the-way place where people don't hunt often and there are lots of things to pull all at once. Trying to do an AOE group in a traditionally highly populated zone with generally respected camps is just lining yourself up for confrontation. You are fine as long as noone is there, but when someone calls a camp check and you shout &quot;Lord/AM/Hand/FG/Sentinel/Ritualist&quot; expect someone to say &quot;Which one? You listed 4 camps there.&quot; Monololizing 4 camps (or even 2) with an AOE group in a loot-oriented zone is disrespectful to the normal players who would be happy with just 1 camp. I'm sure you would probably find a way to work it out with someone to share 1 camp instead of just replying, &quot;AOE groups always monopolize areas and camps - deal with it&quot; becuse I generally think you and the people you play with respect other players. <p>Vulrath Vadrigaar<br>
